      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a powerful judicial tool that allows the Supreme Court to strike down government laws that infringe on fundamental rights, even when those laws don't explicitly violate the text of the Constitution. This concept has been used to expand civil liberties by protecting privacy, reproductive rights, and the right to marry, ensuring that the government cannot arbitrarily interfere with personal autonomy. By interpreting the Fourteenth Amendment broadly, the courts have consistently ruled that the government must respect the dignity and freedom of every individual.",
